<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="356" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1645,1742]" pageId="11" pageNumber="356">Male hindwing without modifications, valva lacking internal circular scale patch, male abdomen without coremata. The spatulate scales at the hindwing anal corner have a serrate distal edge. The species are variable, and in general, dissection of the genitalia is necessary for accurate identification.</paragraph>
